<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF73CEA3FF77F8BCD9373436" pageId="254" pageNumber="255" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF73CEA3FF77F8BCD9373436" blockId="254.[136,778,1901,2072]" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF73CEA3FF77F8BCDA513BA9" bold="true" box="[136,258,1901,1927]" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF73CEA3FE85F8BCD9423BA9" box="[378,529,1901,1927]" italics="true" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">A. fernandezi</emphasis>
(Ríos-Tamayo, 2019, fig. 3 F–H) differ from all other members of the 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF73CEA3FD5EF843D85A3B85" baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[673,777,1938,1963]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="254" pageNumber="255" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassipes">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF73CEA3FD5EF843D85A3B85" box="[673,777,1938,1963]" italics="true" pageId="254" pageNumber="255">crassipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by the legs tibiae lighter that the other articles and by the absence of basal denticles on the base of the embolus (Ríos-Tamayo, 2019, fig. 3 F, H).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF73CEA3FCA0FF4FDE1C3C97" box="[863,1359,158,185]" pageId="254" pageNumber="255" type="description">
